body:
@harpone did **just** copying 
tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/data/python/ops/ suffice when using 1.3 as the base installation ?

For me it gave error
```
File "tf1.3/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/data/python/ops/dataset_ops.py", line 22, in <module>
    from tensorflow.python.data.ops import dataset_ops
ImportError: No module named data.ops
```


I tried copying
../tf1.4/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/python/data  to tf1.3 but then had other errors 

```
value = ds.make_one_shot_iterator().get_next()
  File "tf1.3/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/python/data/ops/dataset_ops.py", line 411, in make_one_shot_iterator
    _make_dataset.add_to_graph(ops.get_default_graph())
  File "tf1.3/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/python/framework/function.py", line 449, in add_to_graph
    self._create_definition_if_needed()
  File "tf1.3/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/python/framework/function.py", line 384, in _create_definition_if_needed
    **self._extra_kwargs)
  File "tf1.3/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/python/framework/function.py", line 999, in _parse_kwargs_as_attrs
    raise ValueError("Unknown keyword arguments: %s" % kwargs.keys())
ValueError: Unknown keyword arguments: ['capture_by_value']

```
